# Shared Arbigent project for QuickPizza Android (Flutter + React Native + Android Native).
# run_e2e_tests.sh replaces __ANDROID_PACKAGE__ with the app under test:
#   - Flutter default:        com.example.flutter_mobile_o11y_demo  (launcher label: QPizza Flutter)
#   - React Native default:   com.quickpizza                        (launcher label: QPizza RN)
#   - Android Native default: com.grafana.quickpizza                (launcher label: QPizza Android)
# All three apps share a "QPizza" launcher label prefix and the same pizza-themed icon.
# LaunchApp uses the package id (not the icon position), so CI passes even when the icon
# is not on the first home page; the AI fallback in bring_app_to_foreground matches on the
# pizza icon + the "QPizza" prefix to cover all three apps without per-app branching.

scenarios:
  - id: "start_app"
    goal: |
      You should see the QuickPizza home screen.

      SUCCESS CRITERIA:
      - You see the QuickPizza home screen with a "Pizza, Please!" button.

      __RECOVERY_BLOCK__

    initializationMethods:
      - type: "Back"
        times: 3
      - type: "CleanupData"
        packageName: "__ANDROID_PACKAGE__"
      - type: "LaunchApp"
        packageName: "__ANDROID_PACKAGE__"
    # CI: first screen + OpenAI vision calls often flake (socket timeout, model hesitation).
    maxRetry: 2
    maxStep: 5

  - id: "request_pizza"
    goal: |
      You should request a new pizza and see a pizza recommendation card with "Love it!" and "Pass" buttons below it.
      As soon as you see the pizza card and those two buttons, OUTPUT "Goal achieved" and STOP. Do not tap either rating button in this scenario.

      WHAT IS A PIZZA RECOMMENDATION CARD:
      - It is an UI element which contains:
        - The name of a pizza
        - Information about the pizza, such as: dough, tool, calories, ingredients

      HINTS:
      - If a pizza recommendation card is partially visible but the "Pass" and "Love it!" buttons are not visible, scroll down once. Do not tap "Pizza, Please!" again.

      __RECOVERY_BLOCK__

    maxRetry: 1
    maxStep: 15

  - id: "rate_pizza"
    dependency: "request_pizza"
    goal: |
      You should tap a rating button and see rating success text below the rating buttons.

      SUCCESS TEXT:
      - The success text will appear below the rating buttons.
      - After tapping "Love it!" or "Pass" → look for: Rated!

      HINTS:
      - If you see the success text, OUTPUT "Goal achieved" and STOP. Do NOT tap anything else.
      - The "Pass" and "Love it!" rating buttons are most likely placed at the bottom of the pizza recommendation view.

      __RECOVERY_BLOCK__

    maxRetry: 2
    maxStep: 18

  - id: "put_app_to_background"
    goal: |
      You should see the Android system home screen (launcher with app icons).
      QuickPizza must go to the background.

      1. Use "Press key: HOME" to go to the Android home screen. Do NOT tap any in-app element (Home/About tabs keep you in the app).
      2. If you see app icons (Play Store, Gmail, QuickPizza, etc.), OUTPUT "Goal achieved" immediately. Do NOT swipe or scroll—you are already on home.

      __RECOVERY_BLOCK__

    maxRetry: 1
    maxStep: 4

  - id: "bring_app_to_foreground"
    dependency: "put_app_to_background"
    # Bootstrap: start the correct task by package (substituted per app). Same YAML works for Flutter and RN.
    # If the UI tree still shows the launcher, the AI follows the ORDERED FALLBACK (icon → pages → drawer).
    initializationMethods:
      - type: "LaunchApp"
        packageName: "__ANDROID_PACKAGE__"
    goal: |
      QuickPizza must return to the foreground after HOME (same for Flutter and React Native builds).

      STEP 0 — After automation: wait 1–2 seconds. If you already see the in-app screen with the "Pizza, Please!" button, OUTPUT "Goal achieved" and STOP. Do not tap launcher icons in that case.

      ORDERED FALLBACK — Only if you still see the Android launcher (not the QuickPizza UI):

      CASE A — Icon on THIS home page:
      - If you see a QuickPizza app icon (pizza-themed icon; the label starts with "QPizza", e.g. "QPizza Flutter", "QPizza RN", or "QPizza Android"), tap it once. Do not guess unrelated icons.

      CASE B — Icon not visible on this page (another home screen or drawer):
      - Try a horizontal swipe from RIGHT to LEFT on the empty WALLPAPER area between the dock and the icon rows (do not start the swipe on Phone, Messages, WebView Browser Tester, Camera, or Gmail). This may move to the next launcher page. Look for QuickPizza again. Repeat at most 3 page changes.

      CASE C — Still no QuickPizza icon:
      - Open the "all apps" / app drawer: swipe UP from the bottom edge of the screen (above the nav bar). Scroll the alphabet list if needed and tap the entry whose label starts with "QPizza".

      AVOID: Do not tap WebView Browser Tester, Phone, Messages, or Camera to "find" QuickPizza unless you must press Home first to recover from a mistake.

      SUCCESS CRITERIA:
      - You see the QuickPizza app UI with the "Pizza, Please!" button (not the launcher).

      __RECOVERY_BLOCK__

    maxRetry: 2
    maxStep: 10
